- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on improving the space and time complexity of string matching algorithms.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also likely as regular expression matching is a common task in natural language processing.
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a possibility as string matching algorithms are often used in computational geometry problems.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a possibility as string matching algorithms involve combinatorial and graph-theoretic concepts.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is a possibility as regular expressions are a fundamental concept in formal language theory.
